Looking at the pattern, you need to extract the last segment after the final / from each Sophis/xxx/value entry, handling semicolon-separated multiple values.
One-liner transformer:

const transformBBUnderlying = (value) =>
  value?.split(';').map(v => v.split('/').pop()).join(';') ?? '';


Examples:
	‚àô	Sophis/258182594/498270.KS ‚Üí 498270.KS
	‚àô	Sophis/143917067/.ls;Sophis/143917215/.ss;Sophis/144160632/.lsc3 ‚Üí .ls;.ss;.lsc3

In your grid column definition (AG Grid / React):

{
  field: 'bbUnderlying',
  headerName: 'BB Underlying',
  valueFormatter: (params) =>
    params.value?.split(';').map(v => v.split('/').pop()).join(';') ?? ''
}


Or if transforming at data load time:

const transformedData = rawData.map(row => ({
  ...row,
  bbUnderlying: row.bbUnderlying?.split(';').map(v => v.split('/').pop()).join(';') ?? ''
}));


